result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeramie C Bartosh was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Fraud Against Financial Institution (Value does not Exceed $500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.82(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Jeramie C Bartosh in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

On Motion of the State, the Court AMENDS count #1 to Theft, contrary to 943.20(1)(a), a Class A misdemeanor

On Motion of the State, the Court ADDS Count #2 to reflect a charge of Fraud against a Financial institution, alleging that on 8/23/14 in the Town of Ixonia, Jefferson County, Wisconsin, the defendant obtained money of a financial institution by means of false representation contrary to 943.82(1) and 943.91(1), a Class A misdemeanor.

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
